<title type="html"><![CDATA[sprite zero basic question]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=532&amp;p=4249#p4249"><![CDATA[
No<br /><br />Sprite zero hit happens as the pixels are actually rendered -- if the sprite pixels are not being rendered, the sprite can't be hit.  Both BG and sprites must be enabled -- and for a collision to occur on the left-most 8 pixels of a scanline, the clip option for both BG and sprites must be off.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=33">Disch</a> — Sun Sep 04, 2005 10:30 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
